The course entails one team-project. Students practice identifying and assessing the problem; delimiting semiotic perspective; mapping the adequate interdisciplinary field; defining and specifying the role of semiotic knowledge and methods within this process; finding a solution, planning and accomplishing it; planning and co-ordinating teamwork.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim is to obtain the know-how of using disciplinary knowledge in assessing and researching practical sociocultural situations and processes, in defining, analysing and finding solutions to actual problems.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  - ability to associate professional knowledge with everyday situations and challenges; - ability to use semiotic theories and methods in identifying, assessing and solving practical problems and to relate them purposefully with approaches in associated fields; - experience in using different research methods when collecting data, analysing it, and interpreting the results; - gaining experience in solving practical assignments, project management and teamwork.
